                <note type="abstract">
                    <bibl>Ephesians (literary tradition)<ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/9598"
                        /></bibl>, one of the <bibl>Pauline Epistles (literary tradition)<ptr
                            target="http://syriaca.org/work/9643"/></bibl>, is extant in Syriac in
                    two major translations, <bibl>Ephesians (Peshitta version)
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/81"
                        /></bibl> and <bibl>Ephesians (Harqlean version)
                            <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/10526"
                        /></bibl> (or "Harklensian").</note>
                <note type="versions">Manuscripts, editions, and titles for the individual versions are found in the records below.</note>
                <bibl xml:id="bib9598-1" type="lawd:Edition">
                    <title level="a">Die paulinischen Briefe: 2. Korinthebrief, Galaterbrief, Epheserbrief, Philipperbrief und Kolosserbrief</title>
                    <title level="m">Das Neue Testament in syrischer Überlieferung</title>
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2450"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp" from="249" to="334">249-334</citedRange>
                    <note>Peshitta (P), Harqlean (H), and patristic quotations shown in parallel.</note>
